text: $MU and $INTC were probably the two most favorably mentioned stocks in the business media in the last two months - there is a lesson there! Fade consensus and "group stink."

The way to be right is to perform hard hitting security analysis. The way to be confident... in a market dominated by momentum products and strategies - well, there is no way to be confident with precision. That's why I always average in...

I so wish I could be as certain (and accurate) regarding market direction than the talking heads I watch on biz TV. My inability helps to explain why I nearly always average in to positions (both long and short). And I typically start small-sized.
